                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Kerhunge did a great guide on Nadox.  It's a bit out of date since they changed the fear pathing (fire pit/campfire is a no go anymore, which is a drag because it used to be cake), but the flip side is that the steps of the shrine now path TOWARD the zone, rather than toward the shrine, which makes it a prime fear kiting location.  All single pulls and the best part is that you can levant straight to the pull spot from the zone in, making it easy to check camp status without having to run through the shrine to get there.  <br /><br />Undead temple is also doable for a level 55 duo.  This is a pet tanking spot, which is why you need a duo at level 55, and heal your pet often, otherwise the 49 pet gets munched (rogue pet = worthless in this spot).</span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
